{
  "stem": "33.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Going left, as we later found out, of course, was immediate death, was to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "The two box cars with hospital patients had absolutely no chance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "There was no selection.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "They were all immediately sent to the left, which, of course, I had no idea about at that point.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Who went to the left?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who didn't have a chance?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Older people did not have a chance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Children, of course, did not have a chance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And mothers with children did not have a chance, because they did not want to create any kind of hysteria by separating them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, this next-door neighbor of mine, who was a-- a younger woman, in her early thirties, in excellent physical shape, really an athlete, but she was holding her older mother by her arm, so she didn't have a chance, because they wouldn't separate them.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would just send both of them to the left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Pregnant women, of course, did not have a chance.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I guess, basically those of us who just at a glance he could tell that he or she is in perfect physical shape even after a miserable journey, and he or she is young enough, strong enough that even under the worst circumstances he can give us some slave labor before he dies or we destroy him, I guess those of us had a chance.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, I think, I have to emphasize the date, June the 3rd of 1944, only three days before D-Day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I suppose the camps were so full that only about 300 of the 3,000 of us did go to the right.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Friends of mine, boys and girls between the ages of 16 and 20, a lot of them never made it to the right for no reason at all, I suppose just sheer arithmetic.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
